⚠️ Important: This practical must be done on Linux (Ubuntu). KVM cannot be installed on Windows directly.

Practical 5 — Steps (Ubuntu / Linux)
1️⃣ Check Virtualization Support

Open terminal and run:

egrep -c '(vmx|svm)' /proc/cpuinfo

Output:

1

If output > 0, virtualization is supported. 

CLOUD COMPUTING AND WEB SERVICE…

2️⃣ Update System
sudo apt update
3️⃣ Install KVM and Required Packages

Run:

sudo apt install qemu-kvm libvirt-daemon-system libvirt-clients bridge-utils virt-manager -y

These packages install:

KVM

QEMU

libvirt

Virtual Machine Manager

4️⃣ Add User to KVM Group

Run:

sudo adduser $USER libvirtd

Then logout and login again.

5️⃣ Verify Installation

Run:

virsh -c qemu:///system list

Output example:

 Id   Name   State
--------------------

Empty list means no VM created yet. 

CLOUD COMPUTING AND WEB SERVICE…

6️⃣ Open Virtual Machine Manager

Run:

virt-manager

GUI window will open.

7️⃣ Create New Virtual Machine

In Virtual Machine Manager:

Click Create New Virtual Machine

Select ISO Image

Choose OS type (Linux/Windows)

Allocate:

RAM
CPU

Create Virtual Disk

Click Finish

8️⃣ Install Operating System

Select Ubuntu / Windows ISO

Start installation

Follow normal OS installation steps.

9️⃣ Start the Virtual Machine

Click:

Start

The VM will boot into the installed OS.

Expected Output
KVM installed successfully
Virtual Machine Manager running
Virtual machine created and started